-- Ganges Boat Capsize Drowns at Least 10 People in India's Uttar Pradesh
-- Jay Shankar
-- 2010-06-14T06:00:12Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2010-06-14/ganges-boat-capsize-drowns-at-least-10-people-in-india-s-uttar-pradesh.html

          
          
             At least 10 people on their way to
perform religious rites drowned when a boat capsized in the
Ganges River in India’s northern state of Uttar Pradesh, a
police official said.  
 More than 20 people are missing while 15 others swam to
safety, Shakeel Ahmed, sub-inspector of police, said in a phone
interview from the state’s capital,  Lucknow . The incident took
place in Ballia, southeast of the city, he said.  
